task.summary: Adds data layer, Redis for domain queue
Adds test templates, test for domainqueue
Refactored messaging layer to expose the queues themselves instead of a single facade
Refactors packages again, added discovered domain processor functionality
Applies a request rate limit to domain consumers, other small bug fixes
Migrates application's environment settings to one static location
Fixes for bugs discovered during testing
Hub publishes larger batch of seeds if queue is empty upon startup
Crawl results now indexed by sha256hash of variable length URL

Queue Managers responsible for publishing and consuming messages now assigned to each queue. Adds global Config state. Adds capacity to compress and decompress gzip'd messages. Fixed bug with Redis set size lookup.

Resolves a ton of headaches from character encoding issues between different systems by converting to base64 before publishing to messenger, adds compression unit tests, adds domain manager for discoveredDomain queue
Fixes bug where Jedispool would grant access to instances of Jedis but never have the instances returned
